         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Presteigne ¶ August 23d 1858 ¶ My dear sir ¶  ¶ Being at this moment from home on a tour in the West of England Sir William Hooker has kindly forwarded to me your letter of the 15th June. I have no he...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">58.08.23a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From George Bentham</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M4, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS black-edged. Bentham’s mother died on 18 May 1858.</p>
               </note>Presteigne</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">August 23d 1858</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Being at this moment from home on a tour in the West of England Sir William Hooker has kindly forwarded to me your letter of the 15th June. I have no hesitation in saying in reply that from the examination I made of it I considered your <name key="Barklya%20syringaefolia">Barklya syringaefolia</name> as a very distinct genus. At the same time the specimen I saw was a very incomplete one but I believe there are now better ones at Kew from your subsequent sendings</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Many thanks for your kind offers of which I may very likely hereafter be tempted to avail myself largely. Sir William Hooker may probably have written to you about the Flora of Australia which I have undertaken to draw up under a Government grant. Shortly after my return to town in October I hope to commence it although I shall have other things on hand which will prevent my giving much time to it this winter</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your paper on <name key="Acacia">Acacia</name>s is I believe in the printer's hands but I have not yet seen proofs<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bentham prepared B59.02.01 for the press. See Lucas (1995).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Yours very sincerely</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>George Bentham</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dr Müller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Acacia">Acacia</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Barklya%20syringaefolia">Barklya syringaefolia</name>
